<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="mt-4 mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> July 31, 2024</p>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>At HighScore ("we," "our," "us"), we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website <a href="http://www.highscore.com" target="_blank">www.highscore.com</a> or use our services. Please read this policy carefully to understand our views and practices regarding your personal data and how we will treat it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <h3>2.1 Personal Information</h3>
            <p>When you visit our website or use our services, we may collect the following personal information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Identity Information:</strong> Name, username</li>
                <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Email address, phone number</li>
                <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Password (we store passwords securely)</li>
                <li><strong>Other Information:</strong> Address, date of birth, preferred services</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.2 Technical Information</h3>
            <p>We may collect technical information automatically as you use our website:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>IP Address:</strong> Your IP address when you access our website</li>
                <li><strong>Browser Information:</strong> Type and version of your browser, browser settings</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Time spent on our website, pages visited, click data</li>
                <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking Technologies:</strong> Cookies and other technologies that track your browsing habits</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Service Provision:</strong> To provide, manage, and enhance our services</li>
                <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To send updates, notifications, and support-related information</li>
                <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> To personalize your experience on our website and services</li>
                <li><strong>Security:</strong> To protect your account and our services from fraud and abuse</li>
                <li><strong>Improvement:</strong> To analyze and improve the performance of our website and services</li>
                <li><strong>Legal Obligations:</strong> To comply with legal requirements and protect our rights</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. How We Share Your Information</h2>
            <p>We may share your personal information in the following situations:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Third-Party Service Providers:</strong> With third-party service providers who help us deliver our services. These providers may only use your information for the purposes specified.</li>
                <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> To comply with legal obligations or to protect our rights and interests.</li>
                <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, or other business transfer involving HighScore.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. We strive to protect your information but cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
            <p>We use cookies to enhance your browsing experience, remember your preferences, and analyze website usage. Cookies are small data files stored on your device. You can manage or disable cookies through your browser settings, though this may affect your ability to use some features of our website.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>Under data protection laws, you have rights regarding your personal information, including the right to access, correct, or delete your data. To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information provided below.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
            <p>
